<subSubSection pageId="251" pageNumber="252" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="251" pageNumber="252">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="251" pageNumber="252">This species, also known as the &quot;Columbia River Tiger Beetle&quot;, was once found along the Columbia, Salmon, and Snake Rivers in north-central Oregon, south-central Washington, and western Idaho [see Leffler 1979a: Fig. 29; Pearson et al. 1997: Fig. 27]. According to Pearson et al. (2006: 81), it is now known only from a few sites along the Salmon River in Idaho.</paragraph>
